%Steps%

Now that you've successfully compiled your newly added Game Mode, you'll need to set **FPSProject** to use **FPSGameMode** as the default Game Mode in this step.

1.	In the **Edit** menu, click on **Project Settings**.

1.	Under the **Project** heading on the left side of the **Project Settings** tab, click on **Maps & Modes**.

1.	Select **FPSGameMode** in the Default GameMode dropdown.

	![](SettingFPSGameMode.png)

1.	Close the **Project Settings** menu.

1.	Click the **Play** button in the Level Editor Toolbar. "We are using FPSGameMode." should be displayed in the upper left corner of the viewport.

	![](SectionResult.png)

1.	Click the **Stop** button in the Level Editor to exit Play in Editor (PIE) mode.

